\f0\b \cf0 CloudFoundry CLI\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 You can deploy the application using the IBM Cloud command-line:\
\pard\tx360\pardeftab720\li360\fi-360\partightenfactor0
\cf0 1.	Install the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/cli/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \ul IBM Cloud CLI}}\
2.	Ensure all configured services have been provisioned\
\pard\tx360\pardeftab720\li360\fi-360\sa180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 3.	Run 
\f2 ibmcloud app push
\f1  from the project root directory\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The Cloud Foundry CLI will not provision the configured services for you, so you will need to do this manually using the IBM Cloud web console ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/services/Cloudant/tutorials/create_service.html#creating-a-service-instance"}}{\fldrslt \ul example}}) or the CloudFoundry CLI (
\f2 cf create-service
\f1  command)[{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://cli.cloudfoundry.org/en-US/cf/create-service.html"}}{\fldrslt \ul http://cli.cloudfoundry.org/en-US/cf/create-service.html}}]. The service names and types will need to match your {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "#configuration"}}{\fldrslt \ul configuration}}.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0

