\cf0 \'95	
\f2 Dockerfile-tools
\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The 
\f2 .dockerignore
\f1  file contains the files/directories that should not be included in the built docker image. By default this file contains the 
\f2 Dockerfile
\f1  and 
\f2 Dockerfile-tools
\f1 . It can be modified as required.\
The 
\f2 Dockerfile
\f1  defines the specification of the default docker image for running the application. This image can be used to run the application.\
The 
\f2 Dockerfile-tools
\f1  is a docker specification file similar to the 
\f2 Dockerfile
\f1 , except it includes the tools required for compiling the application. This image can be used to compile the application.\
Details on how to build the docker images, compile and run the application within the docker image can be found in the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "#run"}}{\fldrslt \ul Run section}}.\
